article.description: Robert Morris tops St. Francis (NY) 71-70 in OT
article.headline: Robert Morris tops St. Francis (NY) 71-70 in OT
article.linkText: Robert Morris tops St. Francis (NY) 71-70 in OT
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Robert Morris scored the first seven points of overtime but needed a touch of luck -- as in a late tip-in from Lucky Jones -- to hold on for a 71-70 nail-biter over St. Francis (Brooklyn) Saturday to clinch the Northeast Conference title. Karvel Anderson scored 31 points for the Colonials (18-11, 13-1 Northeast), the third time this season he's surpassed 30 points. Anderson missed a 3-point try after St. Francis had fought back into the lead and it was Jones who made the putback for the win with 3 seconds left. Brent Jones missed a half-court shot for St. Francis (16-13, 7-7). Jalen Cannon and Lowell Ulmer scored 18 each for the Terriers. The Terriers were pummeled by Robert Morris a month ago, but fought through this game with 16 lead changes and six ties. Cannon scored five straight as the Terriers led with 13 seconds left in OT.
